# Editing a Compute Engine Instance on Google Cloud Platform (GCP)

In this guide, we will walk through the steps to edit a Compute Engine instance on Google Cloud Platform using the web console.

## Step 1: Access Compute Engine in GCP Console

1. Log in to your Google Cloud Platform console.
2. Navigate to the Compute Engine section by clicking on the "Compute Engine" option from the left-hand navigation menu.

## Step 2: Locate the Instance to Edit

1. In the Compute Engine dashboard, locate the instance you want to edit from the list of VM instances.

## Step 3: Take a Screenshot Before Stopping the Instance

1. Before making any changes, take a screenshot before stoping the VM.

## Step 4: Edit the Instance

1. On the instance details page, click on the "Stop" button to stop the instance before making any changes.
2. IF AUTHORIZED press "Stop" in the dialog box.
3. Once the instance is stopped, click on the "Edit" button to modify its settings.

## Step 5: Change the Machine Type

1. In the instance edit page, locate the "Machine type" section.
2. Click on the dropdown menu to select a new machine type that suits your requirements.

## Step 6: Save the Changes

1. Before saving, take a screenshot and wait for authorization.
1. After making the desired modifications, scroll down to the bottom of the page.
2. Click on the "Save" button to apply the changes to the instance.

## Step 7: Verify Changes

1. Once the changes are saved, you can verify the updated instance settings by navigating back to the Compute Engine dashboard.
2. Check the instance details to ensure that the changes, including the new machine type, have been applied successfully.

Congratulations! You have successfully edited a Compute Engine instance on Google Cloud Platform.
